quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,40,"So We took him and his hosts, and dumped them into the sea, for he was blameworthy."
  51,41,"And in ‘Âd (there is also a sign) when We sent against them the barren wind;"
  51,42,"It spared nothing that it reached, but blew it into broken spreads of rotten ruins."
  52,31,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم to them): "
  52,32,"Do their minds command them this [i.e. to tell a lie against you (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)] or are they people transgressing all bounds?"
  52,33,"Or do they say: "
  53,25,"But to Allâh belongs the last (Hereafter) and the first (the world)."
  53,26,"And there are many angels in the heavens, whose intercession will avail nothing except after Allâh has given leave for whom He wills and is pleased with."
  53,27,"Verily, those who believe not in the Hereafter, name the angels with female names."
  54,16,"Then how (terrible) was My Torment and My Warnings?"
  54,17,"And We have indeed made the Qur’ân easy to understand and remember; then is there any one who will remember (or receive admonition)?"
  54,18,"‘Âd (people) belied (their Prophet, Hûd); then how (terrible) was My Torment and My Warnings?"
  55,10,"And the earth: He has put down (laid) for the creatures."
  55,11,"Therein are fruits and date-palms producing sheathed fruit-stalks (enclosing dates)."
  55,12,"And also corn, with (its) leaves and stalk for fodder, and sweet-scented plants."
  56,1,"When the Event (i.e. the Day of Resurrection) befalls."
  56,2,"And there can be no denial of its befalling."
  56,3,"Bringing low (some - those who will enter Hell) Exalting (others - those who will enter Paradise). [Tafsir Ibn Kathir]"